---
const techStack = ['Java', 'React', 'Python', 'Go', 'Azure', 'AKS'];
---

<section id="interests" class="min-h-screen flex items-center bg-slate-950 px-6 py-24">
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto w-full">

    <div data-reveal="from-bottom" class="mb-16 text-center">
      <p class="text-teal-400 text-xs font-semibold tracking-[0.3em] uppercase mb-4">
        What I'm Passionate About
      </p>
      <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-white leading-tight">Interests</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <!-- Programming card -->
      <div
        data-reveal="from-left"
        class="group bg-slate-900/60 border border-slate-800 hover:border-teal-500/40 rounded-2xl p-8 transition-all duration-300"
      >
        <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-teal-500/10 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center mb-6 group-hover:bg-teal-500/20 transition-colors duration-300">
          <!-- Code icon -->
          <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-teal-400" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M10 20l4-16m4 4l4 4-4 4M6 16l-4-4 4-4"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Programming</h3>
        <p class="text-slate-400 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          As a full stack developer, I am currently working with a Java and React stack. For
          infrastructure-related work, I have optimized cloud infrastructure in Azure (AKS)
          using Python and Golang.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
          {techStack.map((tech) => (
            <span class="text-xs text-slate-400 bg-slate-800 border border-slate-700 px-2.5 py-1 rounded-md">
              {tech}
            </span>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Arsenal card -->
      <div
        data-reveal="from-right"
        class="group bg-slate-900/60 border border-slate-800 hover:border-teal-500/40 rounded-2xl p-8 transition-all duration-300"
      >
        <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-teal-500/10 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center mb-6 group-hover:bg-teal-500/20 transition-colors duration-300">
          <!-- Star/spark icon -->
          <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-teal-400" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M11.049 2.927c.3-.921 1.603-.921 1.902 0l1.519 4.674a1 1 0 00.95.69h4.915c.969 0 1.371 1.24.588 1.81l-3.976 2.888a1 1 0 00-.363 1.118l1.518 4.674c.3.922-.755 1.688-1.538 1.118l-3.976-2.888a1 1 0 00-1.176 0l-3.976 2.888c-.783.57-1.838-.197-1.538-1.118l1.518-4.674a1 1 0 00-.363-1.118l-3.976-2.888c-.784-.57-.38-1.81.588-1.81h4.914a1 1 0 00.951-.69l1.519-4.674z"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-4">First Arsenal Game</h3>
        <p class="text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">
          My first Arsenal game at the Emirates Stadium was against Aston Villa on September 22,
          2019. Arsenal won 3–2 thanks to a game-winning free-kick by Pierre-Emerick Aubameyang.
          This was also the game where Nicolas Pépe scored his first Premier League goal from the
          penalty spot. I planned a stopover in London just to watch this game live.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
